665 A.2d 1037 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND v. M. Abraham AHMAD. Misc. (Subtitle BV), No. 32,

Sept. Term, 1995.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Oct. 10, 1995.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the Consent to Disbarment from the practice of law filed by M. Abraham Ahmad, in accordance with Maryland Rule BV 12d2, and the written recommendation of Bar Counsel, it is this 10th day of October, 1995

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that M. Abraham Ahmad, be, and he is hereby, disbarred by consent from the further practice of law in the State of Maryland; and it is further

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall strike the name of M. Abraham Ahmad from the register of attorneys, and pursuant to Maryland Rule BV13, shall certify that fact to *175the Trustees of the Clients’ Security Trust Fund and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State.
